    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban Recruitment companies charging a percentage of your wages to process them.",
        "additional_details": "My Partner worked for a recruitment agency, they got him to sign a contract with a third party agreeing to the wages deduction.\r\nHe was desperate for work and signed, he then realised he was working alongside other agency staff who worked for a reputable company who didn't do that.\r\nHe was not allowed to transfer to the other company.\r\nSo effectively on minimum wage after deduction for processing he was being paid 10% less than the minimum wage.\r\nThis is a con.  It does not take much skill to set up sage or some other pay software,  They are ripping the low paid off and need to be outlawed.",
        "background": "Some recruitment agencies charge a Fee for processing your wages.  They pay your wages to a third party company who processes them and pays the remainder minus 10-20% into your bank.",
